Share any unusual traditions or locations on campus
Campus safety is always around and they do their job. They always make sure everything is how its suppose to be.
There is various clubs and activities for everyone to do and get involved in.
Yes it is great all around however it does depend on the person and how they feel about the school.
I am not fully sure on either unusual traditions and locations because I haven't been much apart of anything yet.

Anything I guess you put your mind to. Some people go out , party, smoke , drink and do whatever they feel like doing. I stay in my room and play video games and hang around others sometimes for fun. There are campus parties set up by different clubs now and then.
For me it's a comfy life because i get to spend a lot of alone time to myself and the beds are good. it is so relaxing.
1) The location is awesome 2) The help for good grades is amazing 3) You only can only loose if you don't put in the effort and not do good.

textAfterTable: Categories Comments Great for these types of students It's great for anybody who like small environments. Being from around a big city, it is relaxing for me to be around a small area for a while. Even though you are in school, it feels like a three month vacation. Tips for prospective students Like any college, work is a must. Being here, it is easy to get distracted to be sure to have strong will power but be sure not to get too overworked. Also, Get involved! Being in a small environment, you get noticed for what you do! So be sure to do stuff. Bang for the buck You will not get views or community like this in many places. People are so close to each other and the area is breathtaking. The college is also great for diversity and small town values. Because of the yearly Field Periods, you can get your foot in the door for careers when you graduate, which you won't find anywhere else, making this requirement priceless! Am enjoying being here You may think Keuka is in the middle of nowhere, but that is far from the truth. Yes, Keuka is in the heart of farm country,
